# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __itruediv__, __ifloordiv__, __imod__ across all 6 decimal subjects
#
# 6 classes x 3 methods = 18 rows.
# All eighteen values are false. KEY FINDING: Decimal defines __truediv__,
# __floordiv__, __mod__, __rtruediv__, __rfloordiv__, __rmod__ but NOT the
# in-place variants (__itruediv__, __ifloordiv__, __imod__). Decimal instances
# are immutable; augmented assignment (d /= x, d //= x, d %= x) rebinds the
# variable to a new Decimal via the forward operator, it does not mutate d in
# place. Consistent with wave 666 pattern: no in-place operators in Decimal.__dict__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

